The rank and file are outraged at all these players involved in the Tony Bosch Biogenesis scandal, players still trying to beat the system after their fellow union members negotiated the most comprehensive drug program in all of professional sports in an effort to clean up baseball once and for all. Outraged enough that, for the first time, there is the suggestion that steroid cheats should have to pay with their contracts. Up until now, baseball contracts have been sacrosanct, as in unable to be voided.
